parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Steer Tire Wear due to Improper Axle Configuration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear on steer tires can lead to reduced traction, increased stopping distances, and a higher risk of tire failure, which can cause accidents.
symptoms: Uneven or excessive wear on steer tires

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear suspension problems can affect vehicle stability and handling, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Unusual noises or vibrations from the rear suspension

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Conditioner Failure due to Bad Wiring
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air conditioner failure can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: unusual noises or smells from the air conditioner

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front tie rod can cause the steering to lock up, making the vehicle hard to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle is hard to control
the steering feels heavy or inoperative

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wiring Harness Failure under the Dash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness under the dash can cause intermittent or complete loss of various dashboard functions, including turn signal indicators, gauges, and instrument panel displays, which can lead to reduced visibility, increased risk of accidents, and decreased vehicle safety.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete loss of turn signal indicators
lines or obstruction on the diagnostic display
loss of contact or corrosion on wiring harness connectors.
